# OMX Control

Small Python helpers for the Robotis OMX arm built on top of the Python bindings from rustypot.

The package keeps the robot-specific movement limits in one place and exposes one safe command path per joint.

## Install

```bash
pip install -e .
```

## Joint map

| Joint | Motor ID | Safe range | Home |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| gripper | 16 | 180° to 250° | 250° |
| base | 11 | 90° to 270° | 180° |
| joint1 | 12 | 78° to 260° | 78° |
| joint2 | 13 | 278° to 90° | 278° |
| joint3 | 14 | 266° to 90° | 266° |
| joint4 | 15 | 360° to 0° | 178° |

## Example usage

The examples use a controller class from rustypot and move only one joint at a time.

Run them from the repository root:

```bash
python examples/basics/test_base.py --serial-port /dev/ttyUSB0
python examples/basics/test_joint1.py --serial-port /dev/ttyUSB0
```

## Notes

The rustypot Python binding expects goal positions in radians. This package accepts degrees at the OMX layer and converts them before sending commands.
